XXVII. Even when sour, wine still has uses as a remedy. Vinegar has very great cooling qualities, being equally efficacious, houex cr, as a lesolvcnt; earth in fact effervesces when vinegar is poured on it. I have often said, and shall often have to say, how often it is a beneficial ingr-edient with other things. Drunk by itselfit removes nausea and chet-ks hiccough, and to smell it stops sneezing.
